{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Continual pre-training involves further training a pre-trained language model on additional data relevant to a specific domain or language, such as Biomedi-cal (Bolton et al., 2024), Mathematics (Azerbayev et al., 2024), or languages like those in Southeast Asia (Dou et al., 2024).",
    "SFT, on the other hand, trains a language model with specific instructions or guidelines to align with specific tasks (Wei et al., 2022) and user preferences via RLHF (Ouyang et al., 2022), using data consisting of pairs of instructions and their corresponding desired outputs.",
    "A key component of both continual pre-training and SFT is the existence of high-quality data, whether synthetic or human-annotated (AI et al., 2024; Liu et al., 2024).",
    "However, annotators for SFT data are predominantly from the age group 18-35 (Table 1), whose distinct linguistic and cognitive preferences, as well as safety needs, differ significantly from those of children.",
    "For example, annotators on Amazon Mechanical Turk (MTurk) must be at least 18 years old."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Continual pre-training involves further training a pre-trained language model on additional data relevant to a specific domain or language, such as Biomedi-cal (Bolton et al., 2024), Mathematics (Azerbayev et al., 2024), or languages like those in Southeast Asia (Dou et al., 2024).",
    "SFT, on the other hand, trains a language model with specific instructions or guidelines to align with specific tasks (Wei et al., 2022) and user preferences via RLHF (Ouyang et al., 2022), using data consisting of pairs of instructions and their corresponding desired outputs.",
